Insider Activity


Individual




Mellody Louise Hobson



Ms. Mellody L. Hobson is Chairman at After School Matters, Inc., Independent Director at Starbucks Corp., Chairman at DreamWorks Animation SKG, Inc., Independent Director at Estee Lauder Cos., Inc., President & Director at Ariel Capital Management Holdings, Inc., Chairman & President at Ariel Investment Trust and a Member at Council on Foreign Relations, Inc. She is on the Board of Directors at Starbucks Corp., Estee Lauder Cos., Inc., Ariel Capital Management Holdings, Inc., Chicago Public Library Foundation, Lucas Museum of Narrative Art, The Chicago Public Education Fund, The Chicago Public Library, The Field Museum of Natural History, World Business Chicago, Investment Company Institute, George Lucas Family Foundation and The Sundance Institute. Ms. Hobson was previously employed as Independent Director by Groupon, Inc., Senior Vice President & Marketing Director by Ariel Capital Management, Inc., a Trustee by Princeton University, and a Member by Reliant Equity Investors LLC. She also served on the board at Tellabs, Inc. She received her undergraduate degree from Woodrow Wilson School of Public & International Affairs.



